node.text:
Organizer. Justice seeker. Educator. Freedom fighter. 

Bob Moses was a civil rights giant and movement architect. May he rest in peace and power.

node.text: I've so many special moments with people each day, people I'm meeting for the very first time & may never see again but the impression they leave on my heart is indelible.This young woman, Hope is one of them. Ps) On Thursdays we wear pink. Shout out to @jprattboutique @dsimagegroup for the fit.

node.text:
Roxbury family! I'm headed back to @frugalbooks on Friday to read @meena's book Ambitious Girl. 

Space is limited, but we hope you can join us. Masks will be required. RSVP today for a chance to receive a copy of the book!

Link in bio 📖

node.text:

Shout out to @burtontoy for convening the community every year in the name of joy 🎉

node.text: A neighbor shared some fresh kale from their plot at the #HydePark community garden & it hit my breakfast smoothie different. A sibling in the food justice movement once corrected me when I used the term "food deserts". She said, "We know how to grow food, that's in our blood, we just need the land to do it. We live in food apartheid systems."

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Ayanna Pressley on July 01, 2021 tagging @ayannapressley, and @joebiden. May be an image of 3 people and people standing.

node.text:
At the White House, President @JoeBiden gave me his word no person in America would be executed on his watch.

I’m grateful for his conviction & this critical announcement from the DOJ.

Our work to end the #deathpenalty once and for all is urgent. A more just world is possible.

node.text:
Black folks deserve joy, rest, celebration, reparations, safety, health care, financial freedom, the chance to witness the end of the carceral state and full liberation. 

#Juneteenth 🖤

node.text:
There have been 21 transphobic killings in the US since the year began. Last weekend, we gathered at Franklin Park to demand an end to the violence. 

But we also gathered together in JOY to celebrate Pride. 

Solidarity with our trans siblings this month and every month 🌈
